Artform: None

Look at the top three cards of your deck. Reserve one of them and put the rest on the bottom of your deck in any order.

Artform: Alchemy

[i](Elixirs provide LL. When an Elixir is used to use a transcend or attack ability, reserve a card from your discard pile.)[/i]

Artform: Writing

[i](Inkwells provide I.)[/i]
A deck can have any number of cards named Inkwell.

Artform: Music

[i](MusicNotes provide {N}. As you reserve a MusicNote, you may turn it face up as a composed note.)[/i]
A deck can have any number of cards named Music Note.

Artform: Alchemy

[i](Potions provide L. At normal speed, you may destroy three Potions you control to create an Elixir token.)[/i]
A deck can have any number of cards named Potion.

Artform: Theater

[i](You may have Masks enter as a ComedyMask or TragedyMask. Swap them at the start of your turn. ComedyMasks provide {C}. TragedyMasks provide {T}.)[/i]
A deck can have any number of cards named Theater Mask.

{A}I: Antagonor transcends 1.
{A}I: Antagonor attacks 1.

{A}{A}II: Inkeye transcends 2. Draw a card.

{C}{C}{C}{C}: Curtainyx transcends 2.
{T}{T}: Curtainyx attacks 1.

{C}{C}: Exitask transcends 1.
{C}{C}{C}{C}{C}: Exitask and another creation you control each transcend 1. and Discard two cards, then draw two cards.
{T}{T}{T}: Exitask attacks 1.

{C}{C}: Actorialle transcends 1. If it has transcended already this turn, it transcends 2 instead.
{T}{T}: Actorialle attacks 1. If it has transcended this turn, it attacks 2 instead.

Artform: Theater

{C}{C}: Glamora transcends 1. Move up to one Transcendence counter from another creation you control onto Glamora.
{T}{T}: Glamora attacks 1.

Artform: Music

{A}{N}: You may reserve a MusicNote card from your discard pile. If you do, Drummaton transcends 1.
{A}{A}{N}: You may reserve two MusicNote cards from your discard pile. If you do, Drummaton and another creation you control each transcend 1.

Artform: Music

At the end of your turn, if you have two or more composed notes, Composivoice transcends 1.
{A}{N}: Composivoice attacks 1.

Artform: Music

At the end of your turn, if you have two or more composed notes, Loudeling attacks 1.
{A}{N}: Loudeling transcends 1.
{A}{A}{N}: Loudeling transcends 1. You may put a card from your reserves into your hand.

Artform: Music

{A}{N}: Squirrecord transcends 1. If you've taken reserve action this turn, Squirrecord transcends 2 instead.
{A}{N}: Squirrecord attacks 1.

Artform: Alchemy

{A}{A}L: Golemouth transcends 1. You may destroy a medium or creation you control. If you do, Golemouth transcends 1 again.
{A}{A}{A}LL: Golemouth transcends 2.
{A}L: Golemouth attacks 1.

Artform: Alchemy

{A}L: Golochet transcends 1.
{A}{A}{A}L: Golochet transcends 2.
{A}{A}L: Destroy any number of mediums and/or creations you control. Golochet attacks X, where X is the number of permanents destroyed this way.

Artform: Alchemy

{A}LL: Walkestalk transcends 1 and attacks 1.
{A}{A}LLL: Walkestalk transcends 2 and attacks 2.

Artform: Alchemy

{A}{A}L: Zombir transcends 1 and attacks 1.
{A}L: Zombir attacks 1.

{A}{A}{N}: Noterat transcends 1. Put a card from your reserves into your hand.
{A}{A}{N}: Noterat attacks 1. Reserve up to two cards from the top of your deck.

Artform: Alchemy

{A}L: You may discard a card. If you do, Pactithorn transcends 1.
{A}{A}{A}L: You may discard a card. If you do, Pactithorn transcends 2.
{A}{A}L: Pactithorn attacks 1.

Up to two target creations can't use attack or transcend abilities this turn.

As a cost to play Prevent, discard two cards.
Target non-Medium card being played is put into its owner's discard pile.

Search your deck for up to two medium cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand.

Artform: Writing

Play Learn from Ink only if you control two or more Inkwells.
Draw two cards, then reserve a card from your hand.

Artform: Writing

Reactive [i](May be played or activated anytime you have priority.)[/i]
Play Drench in Ink only if you control two or more Inkwells.
Play Drench in Ink only if you control six or more Mediums.
Target card being played is put into its owner's discard pile.

Play Siphon Through Ink only if you control three or more Inkwells.
Draw a card. Each opponent discards a card.

Artform: Writing

Play Gift of Ink only if you control two or more Inkwells.
Each player draws two cards.

Artform: Theater

Reactive [i](May be played or activated anytime you have priority.)[/i]
Play Unmanifest only if you control four or more in any combination of ComedyMasks and TragedyMasks.
Put target creation into its owner's hand.

Artform: Theater

Play Mask Crafting only if you control five or more mediums.
Put a Mask from your hand into your play zone.

Artform: Theater

Play Troupe Call only if you control two or more ComedyMasks and two or more TragedyMasks.
Put a Mask from your hand into your play zone.

Artform: Theater

Reactive [i](May be played or activated anytime you have priority.)[/i]
Play Interrupt only if you control a ComedyMask and a TragedyMask.
Detach up to three mediums from target creation.

Artform: Music

Reserve two target MusicNote cards from your discard pile.

As a cost to play this card, trash three of your composed notes.
Draw two cards.

Artform: Music

As a cost to play this card, trash two of your composed notes.
Sonic Flare deals 2 damage to target creation.

Artform: None

Choose one —
• Destroy target modifier.
• Remove a Transcendence counter from target creation.

Artform: Music

Play Seek the Sound only if you've stockpiled this turn.
Search your deck for a MusicNote card, reveal it, reserve it, then shuffle.

Artform: Alchemy

Play Forbidden Knowledge only if you control a Potion or Elixir.
As a cost to play this card, destroy two creations you control.
Draw three cards.

Artform: Alchemy

Play Acid only if you control a Potion or Elixir.
As a cost to play this card, discard a card.
Destroy target non-spectral creation or modifier.

Artform: Alchemy

Play Spirit Bounty only if you control an Elixir.
Modifies creation
When modified creation perishes, draw two cards.

Artform: Alchemy

Play Salve only if you control an Elixir.
Put two cards of the same card type from your discard pile into your hand.

Artform: Writing

As long as there are four or more mediums attached to Roosterror, if another creation you control would deal damage to a creation, it deals that much damage plus 1 instead.
{A}I: Roosterror transcends 1.
{A}I: Roosterror attacks 1.

Artform: Writing

{A}I: Squirius transcends 1. Reserve the top card of your deck.
{A}{A}II: Squirius transcends 2. Reserve the top card of your deck.
{A}{A}I: Squirius attacks 1. Put a card from your reserves into your hand.

Artform: Writing

I: As a cost to activate this ability, destroy any number of mediums attached to Consumptoad. Consumptoad transcends 1 for each medium destroyed this way.
{A}I: Consumptoad attacks 1.

Artform: Writing

{A}{A}I: Inkidrain transcends 1. Draw a card.
{A}{A}{A}II: Inkidrain transcends 1. Draw a card. Each opponent discards a card.
{A}{A}I: Inkidrain attacks 1. Each opponent discards a card.

Artform: Theater

Whenever one or more Transcendence counters are put on Leadette from an ability of another creation, put a Transcendence counter on Leadette for every second ComedyMask attached to it.
{T}{T}: Leadette attacks 1.

Artform: Theater

{C}{C}: Maskraft transcends 1. You may trigger the start of turn ability of a Tragedy.
{C}{C}{C}{C}: Maskraft and another creation you control each transcend 1. Put up to one Mask from your hand into your play zone.

Artform: Music

The first time Songuard would take damage each turn, if you have two or more composed notes, Songuard doesn't take that damage.
{A}{N}: Songuard transcends 1.
{A}{A}{A}{N}: Songuard transcends 2.
{A}{A}{N}: Songuard attacks 1. If you have two or more composed notes, Songuard attacks 2 instead.

Artform: Music

When Soniclasm enters a play zone, you may trash one of your composed notes. If you do, it gains aggressive. [i](If it has aggressive, a creation can use an attack ability the turn it's played.)[/i]
{A}{N}{N}: Soniclasm attacks 2.

Artform: Theater

{T}{T}: Slaughtrestage transcends 1. You may trigger the start of turn ability of a Comedy.
{T}{T}{T}{T}: Slaughtrestage and another creation you control each attack 1.

Artform: Theater

{C}{C}: Spectract transcends 1.
{T}{T}: Spectract attacks 1. Then if the attacked creation is still in play, put it into its owner's hand.

Artform: Music

{A}{A}{N}: Trash any number of your composed notes. Trebbletrash transcends X, where X is half the number of cards trashed this way, rounded down.
{A}{N}: Trash any number of your composed notes. Trebbletrash attacks X, where X is half the number of cards trashed this way, rounded down.

Artform: Music

{A}{N}: Rhythmoss transcends 1. If you have two or more composed notes, Rhythmoss transcends 2 instead.
{A}{A}{A}{N}{N}: Rhythmoss transcends 2.
{A}{N}: Rhythmoss attacks 1.

Artform: Alchemy

{A}L: Vampyre transcends 1 and attacks 1. Discard a card.

Artform: Alchemy

LL: Zombug transcends 1 and attacks 1. Then if this was the first transcend ability you've used this turn, destroy Zombug.

Artform: Alchemy

{A}{A}LL: Ghoulog transcends 1, then attacks X, where X is the number of Transcendence counters on it.

Artform: Alchemy

{A}L: Impyre transcends 1. Put the top card of your deck into your discard pile.
{A}{A}{A}LL: Impyre transcends 2. Put the top three cards of your deck into your discard pile.
{A}L: Impyre attacks 1. If a creation didn't perish from that attack, reserve a card from your discard pile.

Artform: None

As a cost to play this card, put four cards from your reserve into your discard pile.
Draw two cards.

Artform: None

Play Inferno only if you control four or more mediums.
As a cost to play Inferno, put two mediums you control into your hand.
Destroy all creatures.

Artform: None

Put the top four cards of your deck into your discard pile.

Artform: None

As a cost to play Bond Through Time, discard a creation card.
Put target creation card that doesn't share an artform with the discarded card from your discard pile into your hand.
If you've played a card named Bond Through Space this turn, you may put a creation card from your hand into your play zone with two Transcendence counters.

Artform: None

As a cost to play Bond Through Space, discard a creation card.
Search your deck for a creation card that doesn't share an artform with the discarded card, reveal it, put it into your hand, then shuffle.
If you've played a card named Bond Through Time this turn, you may put a creation card from your hand into your play zone with two Transcendence counters.

Artform: None

Choose an artform. Flare of Choice deals X damage to target non-spectral creation, where X is the number of creations and modifiers you control of the chosen artform.

Artform: None

Flare of Void deals X damage to target non-spectral creation, where X is the number of creations and modifiers you control without an artform.

Artform: None

Flare of Flexibility deals 1 damage to target non-spectral creation for each artform among creations and modifiers you control.

Artform: None

Play Negate only if you control two or more mediums.
As a cost to play Negate, discard a card.
Target non-Medium card being played is put into its owner's discard pile.

Artform: None

Play Stifle only if you control four or more mediums.
Target non-Medium card being played is put into its owner's discard pile.

Artform: Writing

Reactive [i](May be played or activated anytime you have priority.)[/i]
Play Inkseep only if you control two or more Inkwells.
Play Inkseep only if you control four or more Mediums.
Target non-Medium non-Creation card being played is put into its owner's discard pile.
Draw a card.

Artform: Writing

Play Inksight only if you control two or more Inkwells.
Play Inksight only if you control four or more Mediums.
Draw two cards.

Artform: Writing

Reactive [i](May be played or activated anytime you have priority.)[/i]
Play Author's Vengeance only if you control two or more Inkwells.
If a creation you control perished this turn, draw three cards.

Artform: Theater

Reactive [i](May be played or activated anytime you have priority.)[/i]
Play Exeunt only if you control a ComedyMask and a TragedyMask.
Put target creation you control and target creation you don't control into their owners' hands.

Artform: Theater

Play Party Scene only if you control a ComedyMask.
As a cost to play Party Scene, remove two Transcendence counters from a creation you control.
Each creation you control transcends 1.

Artform: Theater

Play Battle Scene only if you control a TragedyMask.
As a cost to play Battle Scene, remove two Transcendence counters from a creation you control.
Each creation you control attacks 1.

Artform: Music

Play Bassdrop only if you control four or more mediums.
Put three of your composed notes into your play zone. Destroy them at end of turn.

Artform: Music

As a cost to play this card, reveal two MusicNote cards from your hand and reserve them.
Draw three cards.

Artform: Music

Reveal the top five cards of your deck. Reserve up to two MusicNote cards from among them and put the rest on the bottom of your deck in a random order. Then if no MusicNote cards were revealed this way, reserve the top card of your deck.

Artform: Alchemy

Play Chaos Ritual only if you control an Elixir.
Each player discards two cards. Draw a card.

Artform: Alchemy

Play Reanimate only if you control an Elixir.
As a cost to play this card, discard a card.
Put target creation from your discard pile into your play zone. It transcends 1.

Artform: Alchemy

Play Blasphemous Choice only if you control a Potion or Elixir.
Each opponent destroys a creation they control.

Artform: None

Create a token that's a copy of target creation you control.

Artform: None

As a cost to play Chains of the Void, discard two cards.
Search your deck for two modifier cards without costs, put them onto the battlefield attached to a creation you don't control, then shuffle.

Artform: None

Modifies creation
Modified creation's abilities require {A}{A} more to use.
When Stupor is put into your discard pile from a play zone, draw a card.

Artform: None

Play Wisdom only if you control three or more mediums.
Look at the top five cards of your deck and put them back in any order. You may shuffle. Draw a card.

Artform: None

Reactive [i](May be played or activated anytime you have priority.)[/i]
Rearrange the stack as you choose. [i](Cards or abilities on the stack can't target cards or abilities above them on the stack. If a card or ability with targets on the stack has no valid chosen targets, it is put into its owner's discard pile if it's a card or deleted if it's an ability.)[/i]

Artform: Writing

Only one Transcendence counter may be put on each creation per turn.
{A}I: Calculaw transcends 1.
{A}I: Calculaw attacks 1.

Artform: Writing

{A}{A}II: Put a Transcendence counter on each other creation you control.
{A}I: Each other creation you control transcends 1.

Artform: Writing

If you would create one or more tokens, you may create that many plus one of those tokens instead.
I: Another creation you control transcends 1.

Artform: None

As long as their are three or more mediums attached to Anticipact, cards all players play have reactive. [i](May be played or activated anytime you have priority.)[/i]
{A}{A}: Anticipact transcends 1.
{A}{A}: Anticipact attacks 1.

Artform: Theater

When Comedeus enters your play zone, trigger the start of turn abilities of each TragedyMask you control.
{C}{C}{C}: Comedeus transcends 1, then create a Tragedeus token and move all Transcendence counters from Comedeus to the created token. Destroy Comedeus.

Artform: Theater

When Comedeus enters your play zone, trigger the start of turn abilities of each TragedyMask you control.
{C}{C}{C}: Comedeus transcends 1, then create a Tragedeus token and move all Transcendence counters from Comedeus to the created token. Destroy Comedeus.

Artform: Theater

{C}: Puppetear transcends 1. You may trigger the start of turn ability of a ComedyMask.
{C}{C}{C}{C}{C}: Puppetear transcends 2.
{T}: Puppetear attacks 1. You may trigger the start of turn ability of a TragedyMask.
{T}{T}{T}{T}{T}: Puppetear attacks 2.

Artform: Theater

When Tragedeus enters your play zone, trigger the start of turn abilities of each ComedyMask you control.
{T}{T}{T}: Tragedeus attacks 1, then create a Comedeus token and move all Transcendence counters from Tragedeus to the created token. Destroy Tragedeus.

Artform: Theater

When Tragedeus enters your play zone, trigger the start of turn abilities of each ComedyMask you control.
{T}{T}{T}: Tragedeus attacks 1, then create a Comedeus token and move all Transcendence counters from Tragedeus to the created token. Destroy Tragedeus.

Artform: Music

{A}{N}: Another creation you control transcends 1.
{A}{A}{A}{N}{N}{N}: Another creation you control transcends 1. Draw a card for each of your composed notes.
{N}: Rhythmaster attacks 1.

Artform: Music

As long as there are three or more mediums attached to Symphonor and you have four or more composed notes, transcend abilities you use require 1 less {N}.
{A}{N}: Symphonor transcends 1.
{A}{A}{A}{A}{N}{N}: Each of your creations transcends 1.

Artform: Music

{N}: Temporage transcends 1. Activate only if you have three or more composed notes.
{N}: Temporage transcends 2. Activate only if you have six or more composed notes.
{N}: Temporage attacks 1. Activate only if you have three or more composed notes.

Artform: Alchemy

{A}{A}{A}LLL: Lichisect transcends 1 and attacks 1. This turn, whenever a creation you control uses an ability that would cause it to transcend and attack, copy that ability.

Artform: Alchemy

Whenever you destroy a creation you control, at end of turn, if their are three or more mediums attached to Necrestore, create a token that's a copy of the destroyed creation.
L: Another token creation you control transcends 2.

Artform: Alchemy

Whenever another creation perishes, if there are three or more mediums attached to Ascendighoul and at least one of them is a Potion or Elixir, Ascendighoul transcends 1.
{A}L: Ascendighoul attacks 1.
{A}{A}LL: Ascendighoul attacks 2.

Artform: Theater

Reactive [i](May be played or activated anytime you have priority.)[/i]
Play All the World's a Stage only if you control seven or more mediums.
Each creation you control with a ComedyMask attached transcends 1.
Each creation you control with a TragedyMask attached attacks 1.

Artform: Writing

As a cost to play this card, discard three cards and destroy a creation you control.
Search your deck for any number of Inkwell cards, put them into your play zone, then shuffle. They can't be attached this turn.

Artform: Writing

Play Obsessive Perfection only if you control two or more Inkwells.
Reserve the top card of your deck.
If this is the fourth, eighth, or twelfth time a card you control named Obsessive Perfection has resolved this game, this card fully transcends.

Artform: Theater

Play Masquerade only if you control three or more in any combination of ComedyMasks and TragedyMasks.
Draw seven cards. Put any number of mediums from your hand into your play zone. Then, discard your hand.

Artform: Alchemy

Play March of the Undead only if you control two or more Elixirs.
Put each creation in your discard pile into your play zone.

Artform: Music

Sonic Boom deals 1 damage to target non-spectral creation for each of your composed notes.

Artform: Music

Play Ultimate Rhythm only if you control four or more MusicNotes.
Reserve any number of MusicNote cards in your discard pile.

Artform: Alchemy

Play The Great Mistake only if you control two or more Elixirs.
Put your deck into your discard pile. Void The Great Mistake.
